1.0    EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
The L.S. Starrett Company (Starretts) stores up to 66,528 pounds of propane at the 121 Crescent Street Athol, Massachusetts site in it's 18,000 gallon propane storage tank.  Starretts is required to address the requirements of the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) Risk Management Program (RMP) Regulation 40 CFR 68 and the Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) Process Safety Management (PSM) regulation 29 CFR 1910.119 because they exceed the 10,000 propane regulatory threshold.
There are a number of other vessels throughout the facility that are below the RMP regulatory thresholds including the 1,000 gallon propane generator tank, the 500 gallon propane forklift filling tank and two, 250 pound ammonia storage containers. These chemicals are not required to be reported according to RMP Regulation 40 CFR 68.  A 5,500 gallon methanol storage tank is also located in the facility that is regulated under OSHA PSM Regulation as a flammable liquid.
The executive summary provides an overview of facility specific information that was generated during the development of the RMP. The RMP electronic submittal form was submitted and reviewed by EPA on February 15, 2000 and must be re-submitted to the EPA within five years of the initial submission or sooner under the following conditions:
* No later than three years after a newly regulated substance is first listed by EPA;
* No later than the date on which a new regulated substances is first present in an already covered process above a threshold quantity;
* No later than the date on which a regulated substance is first present above a threshold quantity in a new process;
* Within six months of a change that requires a revised PHA;
* Within six months of a change that requires a revised offsite consequence analysis and defined as a decrease/increase to endpoint by a factor of two; and
* Within six months of a change that alters the program level that applied to any covered process.
